title: Pink Out volleyball game set at Cobden
text:
Pink Out volleyball game set at Cobden 
Cobden High School Beta Club is sponsoring a Pink Out volleyball game on Thursday, Oct 22. The JV game will start at 6 p.m. with a varsity game to follow. 
There will be a pink bake sale and a silent auction. They will also be selling pink out T-shirts. Donations will be collected in pink boots to help Boot Out Cancer. 
All breast cancer fighters/survivors are invited and will be admitted for free. They will register at the door to be honored before the varsity game and invited to take a victory lap with the team. There will be a special halftime dance presentation by grade schoolers. 
All proceeds will go to Cobden Elementary School 2nd grade teacher, Glenna Tripp. Anyone is invited to donate items for a silent auction.
